SIMPLE: microscopical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Microscopical
<hw>Mi`cro*scop"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>microscopique</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the microscope or to microscopy;
made with a microscope; <as>as, <ex>microscopic</ex>
observation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Able to see extremely minute objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why has not man a <qex>microscopic</qex> eye?</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Very small.</def> <specif>Specifically,</specif>
<def>visible only by the aid of a microscope; <as>as, a
<ex>microscopic</ex> insect</as>; also used figuratively; <as>as, a
<ex>microscopic</ex> advantage</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Microscopically</ent>⟦br⟧
